  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Peel and finely chop your<strong> brown onion[s] </strong>into wedges, then top, tail and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into discs and slice your <strong>baby button mushrooms</strong> in half</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and grate your <strong>ginger</strong>, wash then then slice your <strong>pak choi</strong> in half, lengthways and pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1654014533027-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1654014533027-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1654014533027-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1654014533027-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1654014533027-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based,<strong> hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a matching lid, with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>onion wedges,</strong> <strong>carrot discs</strong> and <strong>halved mushrooms</strong> to the dish and cook for 3-4 min or until the vegetables begin to brown</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1654014538049-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1654014538049-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1654014538049-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1654014538049-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1654014538049-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>sushi rice </strong>to<strong> </strong>an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>with 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cover tightly with<strong> tin foil </strong>and put the dish in the oven for 25 min or until all the water is absorbed and the rice is cooked – this is your <strong>sticky rice</strong></p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1654014541114-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1654014541114-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1654014541114-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1654014541114-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1654014541114-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables have softened, add your <strong>diced chicken thigh</strong> to the dish with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until lightly browned</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>soy sauce </strong>and<strong> sriracha</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) in 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[600ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[800ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1654014555040-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1654014555040-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1654014555040-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1654014555040-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1654014555040-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has browned, add your <strong>ground coriander</strong>, <strong>star anise </strong>and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>grated ginger </strong>(you'll use the rest later) to the dish<strong> </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, pour in the <strong>stock </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cover with a lid and place in the oven for 15-20 min or until the vegetables are tender and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your<strong> Chinese-style chicken hotpot</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1654014583079-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1654014583079-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1654014583079-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1654014583079-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1654014583079-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>remaining grated ginger</strong> to a small heatproof bowl with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Heat a pot with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat for 1-2 min or until very hot</p><p>Once hot, carefully pour the heated oil<strong> </strong>into the bowl,<strong> </strong>give it a good mix up and set aside for later – this is your <strong>chilli oil</strong></p><p>Tip: Be careful – the ginger will sizzle from the heat of the oil!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1654014595826-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1654014595826-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1654014595826-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1654014595826-x1000.jpg",
